display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta \in \mathbb {F}(\alpha )]]></fr:tex> be an arbitrary element. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\beta )]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>-subspace of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha )]]></fr:tex>, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\mathbb {F}(\beta ) : \mathbb {F}]\leq [\mathbb {F}(\alpha ) : \mathbb {F}]<\infty ]]></fr:tex>. <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000Y.xml"
addr="nt-000Y"
title="An element is algebraic iff it is the primitive element of a finite extension">Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta ]]></fr:tex> is algebraic</fr:link>, and since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta ]]></fr:tex> is arbitrary, this means the entire extension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha )/\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is algebraic.</fr:p><html:span
